extends layout/_layout.pug
include components/_actions.pug

block variables
	- var page = 'Build';

block content
	a.c-button(href="./") &larr; Home
	img.c-header-img(src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/s.cdpn.io/813538/build.svg")
	h1 Build
	.c-module
		h4 Goal
		p Work with Engineers to finalize design, resolve edge cases, polish, QA and ship a solution.
	h4 Activities you 
		span.u-text--red should 
		| do
	ol
		li Design the unhappy path: Empty, error and loading states, edge cases.
		li Polish the visuals, make it look beautiful and feel enjoyable.
		li Make sure the copy is concise & easy to understand.
		li QA the built UI early and often. Ensure it's high quality, align with your design.
		li Ensure it is fast and low latency. Ensure itâ€™s perceived performance is high.
		li Take ownership of what we will ship and fight for quality. Push for the best possible experience. Look to cut scope, but not quality. Be okay with this resulting in some healthy tension.
	h4 Activities you 
		span.u-text--yellow could 
		| do
	ol
		li Design meaningful micro-interactions and transitions
		li Sit next to engineers and work around tech challenges together
		li Tweak your designs in the browser in response to technical challenges
		li Write HTML/CSS/JS yourself
		li Create Jira/Github issues and ensure they are closed out before shipping
		li Work with the engineering team to ensure our patterns and components are being used correctly or that you're feeding changes back into the design system
		li Work with marketing and stakeholders to finalize content
		li Create a detailed QA and user testing plan with the team
	.c-module.c-module--green
		h4 Output
		p Your design implemented in high quality and shipped.
	+actions('4. Detail', 'detail', 'blue', '', '', '')